            "command": "nix develop --command bash -c '\ngit add src/textual_directives.cc test/regress/1884.test test/regress/1884.ledgerrc\ngit commit --author=\"John Wiegley <johnw@newartisans.com>\" -m \"$(cat <<'\"'\"'EOF'\"'\"'\nfix: strip outer quotes and unescape \\\" in init-file option values\n\nWhen a user specifies a format option such as --balance-format in a\n.ledgerrc init file, the value is read as raw text with no shell\nprocessing. To include spaces, the value must be wrapped in double\nquotes. However, the option_directive() function previously passed the\nouter quotes through to the format parser, causing two problems:\n\n1. The surrounding `\"...\"` appeared as literal characters in the output.\n2. Escaped quotes `\\\"` inside expressions (e.g. `depth_spacer : \"\"`)\n   caused \"Invalid char '\\'\" from the expression parser.\n\nFix option_directive() to detect and handle quoted option values:\n- Double-quoted values: strip outer `\"...\"`, unescape `\\\"` to `\"` and\n  `\\\\` to `\\`, leave all other `\\x` sequences (like `\\n`, `\\t`) intact\n  for the format parser to interpret.\n- Single-quoted values: strip outer `'...'` with no escape processing,\n  matching shell single-quote semantics.\n- Unquoted values: no change to existing behavior.\n\nAdd regression test for issue #1884 using the exact format from the\nissue report (balance format with embedded empty-string expression).\n\nFixes #1884\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nEOF\n)\"\n'",
